article.description: Damarcus Croaker scored 21 points, Gee McGhee added 20 and Murray State beat Harris-Stowe 105-55 on Friday night in Matt McMahon's coaching debut.
article.headline: Murray State blows out Harris-Stowe 105-55
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. -- Damarcus Croaker scored 21 points, Gee McGhee added 20 and Murray State beat Harris-Stowe 105-55 on Friday night in Matt McMahon's coaching debut. Murray State took a 31-10 lead midway through the first half and led the Hornets by 30 at halftime. Wayne Langston had 16 points for the Racers, who held Harris-Stowe to 29 percent shooting and forced 27 turnovers. A.J. Patty added 11 points and Justin Seymour 10. It was Murray State's fourth largest margin of victory at home and its biggest since 2012. Jalen Fletcher led Harris-Stowe with 10 points. The Hornets had just seven assists on 15 field goals.
